<subSubSection id="12C0657E1A34FFF4FF1DFBFE859EFB64" pageId="1" pageNumber="285" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="5A6536F51A34FFF4FF1DFBFE859EFB64" blockId="1.[151,1436,1107,1206]" pageId="1" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="68AEEAE71A34FFF4FF1DFBFE867AFBBF" bold="true" box="[151,276,1107,1133]" pageId="1" pageNumber="285">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Body size median to large. Head elongate, cone-like; rather convergent apically in antero-ventral view; tegmina usually extending over apex of abdomen; fastigium with notch at basal ventral surface, distinct or indistinct; and considerably wider than 1st segment of antennae.
</paragraph>
